From 850a4d156c5e44899931e43cfb266dfeb8d07e85 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SN2 Dev <sn2@dev>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 02:08:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ia64/sn2: call sn_dma_init() from sn_setup() to register DMA
 ops

Without machvec dispatch, nothing was calling sn_dma_init() to set
dma_ops to SN2's custom SHUB-based DMA operations. With SWIOTLB
disabled for SN2 and no DMA ops registered, all DMA operations
failed with ENODEV, preventing network (tg3) and storage drivers
from functioning.

Previously sn_dma_init() was called via the machvec platform_dma_init
function pointer. With compile-time SN2, we call it directly from
sn_setup().
---
 arch/ia64/sn/kernel/setup.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/ia64/sn/kernel/setup.c b/arch/ia64/sn/kernel/setup.c
index e6a5049..d31dc13 100644
--- a/arch/ia64/sn/kernel/setup.c
+++ b/arch/ia64/sn/kernel/setup.c
@@ -487,6 +487,15 @@ void __init sn_setup(char **cmdline_p)
 
 	sn_timer_init();
 
+	/*
+	 * Register SN2 DMA operations.  Must be done before any
+	 * drivers that use DMA are initialized.
+	 */
+	{
+		extern void sn_dma_init(void);
+		sn_dma_init();
+	}
+
 	/*
 	 * set pm_power_off to a SAL call to allow
 	 * sn machines to power off. The SAL call can be replaced
-- 
